Lagos State government on Tuesday announced the discharge of 60 patients from the isolation centres in the state. The state governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu, who announced their discharge, said the patients include 40 males and 20 females, from Yaba, Eti-Osa and Ibeju-Lekki isolation facilities. “The patients, 31 from the Mainland Infectious Disease Hospital, Yaba,19 from the Ibeju-Lekki and 10 from Eti-Osa Isolation Centres were discharged having fully recovered and tested negative in two consecutive readings,” Sanwo-Olu tweeted. “With this, the number of #COVID19 confirmed cases that have been successfully managed and discharged in Lagos is now 321,” he added. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .